body: "## Why (agent-DX defect class, 2026-07-11 maintainer DX directive)\nEvery entry in the maintainer-agent gotchas ledger about output exists because commands negotiated their own contracts: `pm search` takes `--format json|toon` only (`--format table` errors and looks like zero hits), `pm validate`/`pm notes` take `--json` only (wrong flag looks like zero notes), `pm list --json` projects, `pm get --json` wraps under `.item`, comments/notes bodies live at `.text`, `pm activity` ships an always-empty `.activity` decoy next to `.compact_activity` (pm-p3x4). Agents pay for this in retries and silent-empty misreads — the traps ARE the DX problem, per-command memorization is the tax.\n\n## What\nOne flag grammar (same spelling, same accepted values, same default) and one envelope specification (documented shapes for list/get/mutation/diagnostic/annotation results) applied across every command. TOON and JSON stay; projections stay; nothing is removed — existing spellings become aliases tracked by the alias shim (pm-0z7n) with deprecation counters (pm-0mox).\n\n## Sequencing\nLand AFTER ADR pm-pbyu acceptance and on top of the pm-0z7n shim (flags are spellings too); coordinate with pm-cfed (lean JSON redesign — one envelope spec should serve both) and pm-gdi7 (unknown-option suggestions). Walk the full wiring checklist per surface change; token before/after via pm-a22j baseline."
